    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chairs having a triangular seat and three turned legs, popular in 17th-century America and Britain. The seat may be upholstered. The type is heavily inspired by Late Gothic and Early Renaissance three-cornered chairs of continental Europe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047708/Christie's Online (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000002851/Aronson, Encyclopedia of Furniture (1965)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stoelen met een driehoekige zitting en drie gedraaide poten, populair in de zeventiende eeuw in Amerika en Groot-Brittannië. De zitting is soms gestoffeerd. Dit type stoel is in hoge mate geïnspireerd op de driehoekige stoelen die in de late gotiek en vroege Renaissance populair waren op het Europese vasteland.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stuhl mit dreieckiger Sitzfläche und drei gedrechselten Beinen, der im 17. Jahrhundert in Amerika und Großbritannien verbreitet war. Der Sitz kann gepolstert sein. Dieser Typus ist stark vom spätgotischen und frührenaissancezeitlichen Dreiecksstuhl Kontinentaleuropas beeinflusst.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具三角形椅座與三支上粗下細椅腳的椅子，於十七世紀時風行於英美，有些鋪有座墊；此椅具形式概念來自哥德晚期與文藝復興初期的歐陸式三角椅。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
